[normal]Statistical data:[bold]Our own analysis of information received from our tenants suggests that approx
[normal]imately 85% of them will be affected by one or more of the welfare reform measures
[normal].
[normal]Demand for our in-house Welfare Benefits and Money Advice Service has increased by 42% in the previous 12 months.
[normal]Approximately 61% of our tenants are on full or partial Ho
[normal]using Benefit. 
[normal]Approximately 
[normal]40% of our tenants have digital access at home. 
[normal]68% of Horizon tenants have a disability, with 38% living in housing 
[normal]which has been 
[normal]purpose built or adapted for their needs.
[normal]Affected by the social size criteria: 19% of workin
[normal]g age Horizon tenants 
[normal]                                                               18% of working age 
[normal]Larkfield
[normal] tenants
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]     6% of working age Link tenants 
[normal]43% of working age Horizon tenants affected live in and need housing built to wheelchair use
[normal]r standard (there is clearly a disproportionate impact on disabled people
[normal])
[normal].
